{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:27:26.795235+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 79ab8c039c4c3d3a54677f692f847917ad9dc553)", "id": "lc_9d393092-7faf-42dd-b018-9494fecb4521"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n\n<script setup>\nimport DefaultFooter from './DefaultFooter.vue'\nimport DefaultNav from './DefaultNav.vue'\n\ndefineOptions({\n  name: 'DefaultLayout',\n})\n</script>\n\n<style lang=\"scss\">\n/* Sticky footer */\nhtml {\n  position: relative;\n  min-height: 100%;\n}\nbody {\n  margin-bottom: 60px; /* Margin bottom equal to footer height */\n}\n.default-page-wrapper {\n  padding: 5em 0em 3em 0em;\n}\n.footer {\n  position: absolute;\n  bottom: 0;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 60px; /* Footer height */\n  line-height: 60px; /* Vertically center the text */\n  background-color: $gray-100;\n  text-align: center;\n}\n</style>\n", "id": "lc_6b387bc3-d840-450a-8351-90203287e149"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0a6fe116-1b77-4a03-8bc9-a42e150b1352", "tool_call_id": "call_d857d586bb2846baacdaf2bb", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:27:26.814142+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 24a7906a86ab84affe8e73baf8e3e38691985225)", "id": "lc_b75cdcb5-2226-41d4-9e75-83d91ad24a9d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<template>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <h1>This is the about page</h1>\n  </div>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nexport default {\n  name: 'About',\n}\n</script>\n", "id": "lc_dd559e67-0781-4978-af70-d2b5ec9ddb27"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "af5c71b3-4e07-45c1-8e78-ff13dc0e9dd4", "tool_call_id": "call_4109ae67710a4460b53bc642", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:27:51.497096+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here is how the app bootstraps routing and layout rendering, and how the About page is loaded:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Entry Point — `src/main.js`\n\n```js\nconst app = createApp(App)\n\napp.component('LayoutDefault', Default)   // global component\napp.use(createPinia())\napp.use(router)\napp.mount('#app')\n```\n\nThree key steps happen here:\n\n| Step | What it does |\n|------|-------------|\n| `app.component('LayoutDefault', Default)` | Registers the default layout as a **globally available Vue component** named `LayoutDefault`. This is critical for the dynamic layout trick used in `App.vue`. |\n| `app.use(router)` | Installs vue-router so `<RouterView>` works and route navigation is active. |\n| `app.mount('#app')` | Mounts the root `App.vue` to the DOM. |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Router — `src/router/index.js`\n\n```js\nconst history = createWebHashHistory()   // hash-based URLs (/#/about)\n\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,                     // eagerly imported\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    component: () => import('../views/About.vue'),   // ← lazy-loaded\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n]\n\nconst router = createRouter({ linkActiveClass: 'active', history, routes })\n```\n\nKey observations:\n\n- **Hash-based history** (`createWebHashHistory`) — URLs look like `/#/about`.\n- Each route carries `meta: { layout: 'default' }`, which `App.vue` reads to pick the right layout shell.\n- The **Home** route eagerly imports `Home.vue` (bundled in the main chunk).\n- The **About** route uses a **dynamic `import()`** — `About.vue` is placed in its own separate chunk (`about.[hash].js`) and only fetched when the user actually navigates to `/about`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Root Component & Dynamic Layout — `src/App.vue`\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <component :is=\"layout\">\n    <RouterView />\n  </component>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nexport default {\n  name: 'App',\n  computed: {\n    layout() {\n      return `layout-${this.$route.meta.layout || 'default'}`\n    },\n  },\n}\n</script>\n```\n\nThis is the clever part:\n\n1. The computed property `layout` reads the current route's `meta.layout` (e.g. `'default'`) and prepends `layout-` → produces the string **`\"layout-default\"`**.\n2. Vue's `<component :is=\"layout\">` is a **dynamic component** — it resolves the string `\"layout-default\"` to the **globally registered component `LayoutDefault`** (registered in `main.js`).\n3. `<RouterView />` is passed into that layout component **as the default slot**.\n\nThis means the layout is **entirely driven by route metadata** — change `meta.layout` on a route and a different layout shell renders around the page content.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Default Layout — `src/layouts/default/Default.vue`\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />     <!-- navigation bar -->\n    <slot />           <!-- ← the routed page component goes here -->\n    <DefaultFooter />  <!-- footer -->\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\nThe layout is a simple three-part shell:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────┐\n│       DefaultNav        │\n├─────────────────────────┤\n│                         │\n│   <slot />              │  ← receives Home.vue or About.vue\n│   (routed page content) │\n│                         │\n├─────────────────────────┤\n│      DefaultFooter      │\n└─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\nCSS positions the footer as `position: absolute; bottom: 0` for a sticky-footer effect.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How the About Page Loads — Step by Step\n\nWhen a user clicks a link to `/#/about`:\n\n| Step | What happens |\n|------|-------------|\n| **1** | Vue Router matches the `/about` route. |\n| **2** | The route's `component` is a **lazy dynamic import**: `() => import('../views/About.vue')`. Vue Router triggers this import, causing the browser to **fetch the separate `about.[hash].js` chunk** on demand (code splitting). |\n| **3** | `App.vue`'s computed `layout` resolves to `\"layout-default\"` (from `meta.layout`), so the globally registered `LayoutDefault` component renders. |\n| **4** | `<RouterView />` resolves to the now-loaded `About.vue` component and renders it inside `LayoutDefault`'s `<slot />`. |\n| **5** | The user sees the About page content (`<h1>This is the about page</h1>`) sandwiched between the nav bar and footer. |\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe architecture follows a **layout-per-route** pattern powered by three pieces working together:\n\n1. **Route meta** (`meta: { layout: 'default' }`) — declares which layout each route wants.\n2. **Global layout registration** (`app.component('LayoutDefault', Default)`) — makes layouts available by name.\n3. **Dynamic `<component :is>` in `App.vue`** — resolves the meta string to the actual layout component at render time.\n\nRoute components (Home, About) are **slot-fed** into the layout, and the About page specifically benefits from **lazy loading** — it's only downloaded when needed, keeping the initial bundle smaller.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 2109, "prompt_tokens": 7815, "total_tokens": 9924, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 884, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7296, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006836088, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 9.30888e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00059052}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871246-yLkenpX3DsYKCrFGMeUC", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "l